Comandos para criar e executar o ambiente Nginx com a página "Alô Professor":

1. Inicie o container:
bash

docker run -it -u root deltamir/terraform-ansible:1.8.0 /bin/bash

2. Crie o arquivo de inventário hosts.ini:
bash

echo "[local]" > hosts.ini
echo "localhost ansible_connection=local" >> hosts.ini

3. Crie o playbook playbook.yml:
bash

echo "---" > playbook.yml
echo "- hosts: localhost" >> playbook.yml
echo "  become: yes" >> playbook.yml
echo "  tasks:" >> playbook.yml
echo "    - name: Instalar nginx" >> playbook.yml
echo "      apt:" >> playbook.yml
echo "        name: nginx" >> playbook.yml
echo "        state: present" >> playbook.yml
echo "        update_cache: yes" >> playbook.yml
echo "    - name: Criar pagina HTML" >> playbook.yml
echo "      copy:" >> playbook.yml
echo "        content: '<h1>Alo Professor</h1>'" >> playbook.yml
echo "        dest: /var/www/html/index.html" >> playbook.yml
echo "    - name: Iniciar nginx" >> playbook.yml
echo "      service:" >> playbook.yml
echo "        name: nginx" >> playbook.yml
echo "        state: started" >> playbook.yml

4. Execute o playbook:
bash

ansible-playbook playbook.yml -i hosts.ini

5. Verifique se está funcionando:
bash

curl http://localhost

O resultado esperado é:
html<h1>Alo Professor</h1>

Obs: O -it mantém o terminal interativo. Todo o trabalho acontece dentro do container, sem necessidade de montar volumes do Windows.
